dlinkSwQosMIB.name: dlinkSwQosMIB

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

1.Add a new parameter, percent <value 1-100 >, to set the rate by percentage. -- dQosBandwidthRxRateMode,dQosBandwidthTxRateMode, -- dQosQueueBandwidthMinRateMode,dQosQueueBandwidthMinRateMode 2.change the value range of -- dQosBandwidthRxRate,dQosBandwidthTxRate, -- dQosQueueBandwidthMinRate,dQosQueueBandwidthMaxRate

1.Add police action: replaceCos,replaceAll -- DlinkQosPoliceActionType -- dQosAggPolicerEntry -- dQosAggPolicerConformReplaceCos -- dQosAggPolicerExceedReplaceCos -- dQosAggPolicerViolateReplaceCos -- dQosPoliceEntry -- dQosPoliceConformReplaceCos -- dQosPoliceExceedReplaceCos -- dQosPoliceViolateReplaceCos

dlinkSwQosMIB.description: The Structure of QoS Infomation for the proprietary enterprise.

DlinkQosPoliceActionType.name: DlinkQosPoliceActionType
DlinkQosPoliceActionType.description: A value represents a type of policing action. notApplicable - The action is not specified or not applicable. drop - drop the packet. permit - transmit the packet. replaceDscp - Replace the DSCP value of packet with the configured value. The new DSCP value must be accompanied for use with DlinkQosPoliceActionType. replaceCos - Replace the COS value of packet with the configured value. The new COS value must be accompanied for use with DlinkQosPoliceActionType. replaceAll - Replace both the DSCP and COS value of packet with the configured value.

dQosPolicyMapTable.name: dQosPolicyMapTable
dQosPolicyMapTable.description: This table consists of a list of QoS policy maps.

dQosPolicyMapEntry.name: dQosPolicyMapEntry
dQosPolicyMapEntry.description: An entry defines a QoS policy map.

dQosPolicyMapName.name: dQosPolicyMapName
dQosPolicyMapName.description: This object indicates name of the policy map.

dQosPolicyMapRowStatus.name: dQosPolicyMapRowStatus
dQosPolicyMapRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

dQosPolicyMapCfgTable.name: dQosPolicyMapCfgTable
dQosPolicyMapCfgTable.description: This table consists of a list of QoS policies for the class in a policy map.

dQosPolicyMapCfgEntry.name: dQosPolicyMapCfgEntry
dQosPolicyMapCfgEntry.description: An entry consists QoS policies regarding setting the new precedence field, DSCP field, and CoS field of the out-going packet. The first two index elements identify the policy map class to which the setting policies belong. Multiple objects in a same row can be set for a class if they are not conflicting. As an example of conflicting setting: precedence and DSCP cannot be set at a same row.

dQosPolicyMapCfgSetCosQueue.name: dQosPolicyMapCfgSetCosQueue
dQosPolicyMapCfgSetCosQueue.description: Indicates the new CoS queue. The special value of -1 means the setting is un-configured.

dQosPolicyMapCfgSetCos.name: dQosPolicyMapCfgSetCos
dQosPolicyMapCfgSetCos.description: Indicates the new Cos. The special value of -1 means the setting is un-configured.

dQosPolicyMapCfgSetDscpOnlyIp.name: dQosPolicyMapCfgSetDscpOnlyIp
dQosPolicyMapCfgSetDscpOnlyIp.description: This object indicates whether only remark IPv4 DSCP. 'true' - Only IPv4 DSCP will be marked. 'false'- Both IPv4 and IPv6 DSCP will be marked. This object is meaningful only when dQosPolicyMapCfgSetDscp is configured.

dQosPolicyMapCfgSetDscp.name: dQosPolicyMapCfgSetDscp
dQosPolicyMapCfgSetDscp.description: Indicates the new DSCP. The special value of -1 means the setting is un-configured.

dQosPolicyMapCfgSetPreceOnlyIp.name: dQosPolicyMapCfgSetPreceOnlyIp
dQosPolicyMapCfgSetPreceOnlyIp.description: This object indicates whether only remark IPv4 precedence. 'true' - Ipv4 precedence will be marked. 'false' - Both IPv4 and IPv6 precedence will be marked. For IPv6 packets, the precedence is most three significant bits of traffic class of IPv6 header. This object is meaningful only when dQosPolicyMapCfgSetPrecedence is configured.

dQosPolicyMapCfgSetPrecedence.name: dQosPolicyMapCfgSetPrecedence
dQosPolicyMapCfgSetPrecedence.description: Indicates the new ip precedence. The special value of -1 means the setting is un-configured.

dQosPolicyMapCfgRowStatus.name: dQosPolicyMapCfgRowStatus
dQosPolicyMapCfgRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

dQosClassMapTable.name: dQosClassMapTable
dQosClassMapTable.description: This table consists of a list of QoS type class map.

dQosClassMapEntry.name: dQosClassMapEntry
dQosClassMapEntry.description: An entry defines a QoS class map.

dQosClassMapName.name: dQosClassMapName
dQosClassMapName.description: This object indicates the name of the class map.

dQosClassMapType.name: dQosClassMapType
dQosClassMapType.description: This object indicates how to evaluate multiple match criteria. matchAny - statements in the class map will be evaluated based on the logical OR. matchAll - statements in the class map will be evaluated based on the logical AND.

dQosClassMapRowStaus.name: dQosClassMapRowStaus
dQosClassMapRowStaus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

dQosClassMapCfgTable.name: dQosClassMapCfgTable
dQosClassMapCfgTable.description: This table consists of a list of criteria for class maps.

dQosClassMapCfgEntry.name: dQosClassMapCfgEntry
dQosClassMapCfgEntry.description: An entry defines a match criterion for a class map. The first index element identifies the class map to which the criterion belongs.

dQosClassMapCfgMatchId.name: dQosClassMapCfgMatchId
dQosClassMapCfgMatchId.description: This index is automatically assigned for the match criterion in a class map.

dQosClassMapCfgMatchType.name: dQosClassMapCfgMatchType
dQosClassMapCfgMatchType.description: This object indicates the matching type of the entry. A QoS class map can contain multiple match statements. The dQosClassMapMatchType determines the valid range and value of dQosClassMapMatchValue. accessList - Uses an access-list as matching criterion. cos - matching IEEE 802.1Q CoS value innerCos - matching innermost CoS value of QinQ packets dscp - matching DSCP value and this criterion is applied for IPv4 and IPv6 packets. ipDscp - matching DSCP of IPv4 packets only. precedence - matching precedence and this criterion is applied for IPv4 and IPv6 packets. ipPrecedence - matching precedence of IPv4 packets only. protocol - matching protocol. vlan - matching VLAN ID. innerVlan - matching innermost VLAN ID.

dQosClassMapCfgMatchValue.name: dQosClassMapCfgMatchValue
dQosClassMapCfgMatchValue.description: A dQosClassMapMatchValue is always interpreted within the context of a dQosClassMapMatchType value. The table below explains how to determine the values and ranges of dQosClassMapMatchValue. QoS class map match configuration table ==================================================== Match Type Element Value dQosClassMapMatchType dQosClassMapMatchValue ======================= ============================ accessList DisplayString (SIZE(1..32)) (Note #1) cos OCTET STRING (SIZE(1)) (Note #2) innerCos OCTET STRING (SIZE(1)) (Note #2) dscp OCTET STRING (SIZE(8)) (Note #3) ipDscp OCTET STRING (SIZE(8)) (Note #3) precedence OCTET STRING (SIZE(1)) (Note #4) ipPrecedence OCTET STRING (SIZE(1)) (Note #4) protocol DisplayString (Note #5) vlan OCTET STRING (SIZE(2)) (Note #6) innerVlan OCTET STRING (SIZE(2)) (Note #6) =================================================================== Note#1: This object indicates the name of the access-list to be matched. Note#2: The one octet specifies eight CoSs. The most significant bit represents CoS 0 and the least significant bit represents CoS 7. If the corresponding bit is '1' indicates that CoS is included in the criterion; '0' means the CoS is not included. Note#3: The eight octets specify 64 DSCPs. Each octet within this value specifies a set of eight DSCPs. The first octet specifies first 8 DSCPs: 0 - 7, the second octet specifies the next 8 DSCPs, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered DSCP, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered DSCP. If the corresponding bit is '1' indicates that DSCP is included in the criterion; '0' means the DSCP is not included. Note#4: The one octet specifies eight precedence values. The most significant bit represents precedence 0 and the least significant bit represents precedence 7. If the corresponding bit is '1' indicates that precedence is included in the criterion; '0' means the precedence is not included. Note#5: The element value needs choose the exact case-sensitive string. Supported Protocols that can be matched: arp IP Address Resolution Protocol (ARP) bgp Border Gateway Protocol dhcp Dynamic Host Configuration dns Domain Name Server lookup egp Exterior Gateway Protocol ftp File Transfer Protocol ip (version 4) ipv6 (version 6) netbios NetBIOS nfs Network File System ntp Network Time Protocol ospf Open Shortest Path First pppoe Point-to-Point Protocol over Ethernet rip Routing Information Protocol rtsp Real-Time Streaming Protocol ssh Secured shell telnet Telnet tftp Trivial File Transfer Protocol Note#6: The element value is VLAN ID to be matched. The first octet indicates the high byte of VLAN ID and the second octet indicates the low byte. For example, VLAN ID 1029 is encoded in '0405'H.

dQosClassMapCfgRowStaus.name: dQosClassMapCfgRowStaus
dQosClassMapCfgRowStaus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

dQosServicePolicyTable.name: dQosServicePolicyTable
dQosServicePolicyTable.description: This table consists of a list of interface-specific policy-map associations.

dQosServicePolicyEntry.name: dQosServicePolicyEntry
dQosServicePolicyEntry.description: An entry defines a policy-map association on an interface.

dQosServicePolicyDirection.name: dQosServicePolicyDirection
dQosServicePolicyDirection.description: This object indicates the direction of the policy map is applied: input: for ingress flow outout: for egress flow

dQosServicePolicyName.name: dQosServicePolicyName
dQosServicePolicyName.description: Indicates the name of a service policy map to be attached.

dQosServicePolicyRowStaus.name: dQosServicePolicyRowStaus
dQosServicePolicyRowStaus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

dQosSchedulingModeTable.name: dQosSchedulingModeTable
dQosSchedulingModeTable.description: This table consists of a list of scheduling mechanism configurations for ports.

dQosSchedulingModeEntry.name: dQosSchedulingModeEntry
dQosSchedulingModeEntry.description: An entry configures the scheduling mode on an interface.

dQosSchedulingMode.name: dQosSchedulingMode
dQosSchedulingMode.description: This object indicates the mechanism of QoS scheduling on the interface.

dQosScheduleWrrWeightTable.name: dQosScheduleWrrWeightTable
dQosScheduleWrrWeightTable.description: This table consists of a list of configurations for WRR queue bandwidth of queues.

dQosScheduleWrrWeightEntry.name: dQosScheduleWrrWeightEntry
dQosScheduleWrrWeightEntry.description: An entry defines WRR weight of a queue on an interface. An entry exists for each queue if the WRR bandwidth is configurable on the queue.

dQosScheduleWrrWeightQueueId.name: dQosScheduleWrrWeightQueueId
dQosScheduleWrrWeightQueueId.description: This object indicates the queue ID of the entry.

dQosScheduleWrrWeightValue.name: dQosScheduleWrrWeightValue
dQosScheduleWrrWeightValue.description: Specifies the weight in terms of frame count for the queue.

dQosScheduleWdrrWeightTable.name: dQosScheduleWdrrWeightTable
dQosScheduleWdrrWeightTable.description: This table consists of a list of configurations for WDRR queue bandwidth of queues.

dQosScheduleWdrrWeightEntry.name: dQosScheduleWdrrWeightEntry
dQosScheduleWdrrWeightEntry.description: An entry defines WDRR weight of a queue on an interface. An entry exists for each queue if the WDRR bandwidth is configurable on the queue.

dQosScheduleWdrrWeightQueueId.name: dQosScheduleWdrrWeightQueueId
dQosScheduleWdrrWeightQueueId.description: This object indicates the queue ID of the entry.

dQosScheduleWdrrWeightValue.name: dQosScheduleWdrrWeightValue
dQosScheduleWdrrWeightValue.description: Specifies the weight in terms of frame length count for the queue.

dQosBandwidthCtrlTable.name: dQosBandwidthCtrlTable
dQosBandwidthCtrlTable.description: A table consists of a list of configurations for bandwidth control on interfaces.

dQosBandwidthCtrlEntry.name: dQosBandwidthCtrlEntry
dQosBandwidthCtrlEntry.description: An entry configures the bandwidth on an interface. An entry will exist for every applicable port.

dQosBandwidthRxRate.name: dQosBandwidthRxRate
dQosBandwidthRxRate.description: This object indicates Rx Rate of the specified port. The special value of -1 indicates there is no bandwidth limit for ingress packets. It is based on the dQosBandwidthRxRateMode field and if the dQosBandwidthRxRateMode selected as: rate: means ingress rate limit(units:kbps) and the effective rangs are 8 ~ 10240000. percent: means the percentage and the effective rangs are 1 ~ 100.

dQosBandwidthRxBurst.name: dQosBandwidthRxBurst
dQosBandwidthRxBurst.description: This object indicates the limit for ingress burst traffic in kilobytes. The special value of -1 indicates the limit for ingress burst traffic is unspecified and the limit will follow the setting of dQosBandwidthRxRate.

dQosBandwidthTxRate.name: dQosBandwidthTxRate
dQosBandwidthTxRate.description: This object indicates Tx Rate of the specified port. The special value of -1 indicates there is no bandwidth limit for egress packets. It is based on the dQosBandwidthTxRateMode field and if the dQosBandwidthTxRateMode selected as: rate: means egress rate limit(units:kbps) and the effective rangs are 8 ~ 10240000. percent: means the percentage and the effective rangs are 1 ~ 100.

dQosBandwidthTxBurst.name: dQosBandwidthTxBurst
dQosBandwidthTxBurst.description: This object indicates the limit for egress burst traffic in kilobytes. The special value of -1 indicates the limit for egress burst traffic is unspecified and the limit will follow the setting of dQosBandwidthTxRate.

dQosBandwidthRxRateMode.name: dQosBandwidthRxRateMode
dQosBandwidthRxRateMode.description: This object indicates Rx Rate Mode. It will indicate the field:dQosBandwidthRxRate attribute. rate: means the rate limit. percent: means the percentage.

dQosBandwidthTxRateMode.name: dQosBandwidthTxRateMode
dQosBandwidthTxRateMode.description: Indicates Tx Rate Mode. It will indicate the field:dQosBandwidthTxRate attribute. rate: means the rate limit. percent: means the percentage.

dQosQueueBandwidthCtrlTable.name: dQosQueueBandwidthCtrlTable
dQosQueueBandwidthCtrlTable.description: A table contains information about queue-specific bandwidth control of ports.

dQosQueueBandwidthCtrlEntry.name: dQosQueueBandwidthCtrlEntry
dQosQueueBandwidthCtrlEntry.description: An entry contains bandwidth control information of a queue on a port.

dQosQueueBandwidthQueId.name: dQosQueueBandwidthQueId
dQosQueueBandwidthQueId.description: Indicates the queue ID of the entry.

dQosQueueBandwidthMinRate.name: dQosQueueBandwidthMinRate
dQosQueueBandwidthMinRate.description: Indicates the minimum rate of the specified port and queue. A special value of -1 means no limit. It is based on the dQosQueueBandwidthMinRateMode field and if the dQosQueueBandwidthMinRateMode selected as: rate: means egress Minimum Rate (units:kbps),range are 8 ~ 10240000. percent: means the percentage and the effective rangs are 1 ~ 100.

dQosQueueBandwidthMaxRate.name: dQosQueueBandwidthMaxRate
dQosQueueBandwidthMaxRate.description: Indicates the maximum rate of the specified port and queue. A special value of -1 means no limit. It is based on the dQosQueueBandwidthMaxRateMode field and if the dQosQueueBandwidthMaxRateMode selected as: rate: means egress Maximum Rate (units:kbps),range are 8 ~ 10240000. percent: means the percentage and the effective rangs are 1 ~ 100.

dQosQueueBandwidthMinRateMode.name: dQosQueueBandwidthMinRateMode
dQosQueueBandwidthMinRateMode.description: Indicates the Minimum Rate Mode. It will indicate the field:dQosQueueBandwidthMinRate attribute. rate: means the Minimum Rate. percent: means the percentage.

dQosQueueBandwidthMaxRateMode.name: dQosQueueBandwidthMaxRateMode
dQosQueueBandwidthMaxRateMode.description: Indicates the Maximum Rate Mode. It will indicate the field:dQosQueueBandwidthMaxRate attribute. rate: means the Maximum Rate. percent: means the percentage.

dQosPortIfQueuingTable.name: dQosPortIfQueuingTable
dQosPortIfQueuingTable.description: This table provides port-specific configuration for QoS queuing.

dQosPortIfQueuingEntry.name: dQosPortIfQueuingEntry
dQosPortIfQueuingEntry.description: An entry consists of information for QoS queueing on a port.

dQosPortIf8021pOverride.name: dQosPortIf8021pOverride
dQosPortIf8021pOverride.description: This object indicates whether override the CoS of the packets with default CoS (dot1dPortDefaultUserPriority). If this object is 'true', the default CoS will be applied to all incoming packets, either tagged or untagged, received by the port.

dQosPortIfTrustMode.name: dQosPortIfTrustMode
dQosPortIfTrustMode.description: This object indicates QoS trust mode of the port.

dQosDscpMutationMapTable.name: dQosDscpMutationMapTable
dQosDscpMutationMapTable.description: This table provides a mechanism to create/delete a DSCP mutation map.

dQosDscpMutationMapEntry.name: dQosDscpMutationMapEntry
dQosDscpMutationMapEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the dQosDscpMutationMapTable.

dQosDscpMutationMapName.name: dQosDscpMutationMapName
dQosDscpMutationMapName.description: This object indicates the name of the DSCP mutation map.

dQosDscpMutationMapRowStatus.name: dQosDscpMutationMapRowStatus
dQosDscpMutationMapRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

dQosDscpMutationMapCfgTable.name: dQosDscpMutationMapCfgTable
dQosDscpMutationMapCfgTable.description: The table provides a list of the DSCP mapping of mutations maps.

dQosDscpMutationMapCfgEntry.name: dQosDscpMutationMapCfgEntry
dQosDscpMutationMapCfgEntry.description: Each row contains the mapping from old DSCP value to new DSCP value per specific mutation table. The first index element identifies the mutation map (dQosDscpMutationMapEntry) that a DSCP mapping (dQosDscpMutationMapCfgEntry) belongs to. When a mutation map is removed, the corresponding DSCP mapping configuration will be deleted.

dQosDscpMutationNewDscp.name: dQosDscpMutationNewDscp
dQosDscpMutationNewDscp.description: This object indicates the new DSCP value which the old DSCP values maps to for a specific mutation map. The default mapping of old DSCP to new DSCP for mutation purpose is the identity function, i.e. dQosDscpMutationNewDscp equals to dQosDscpMutationOldDscp

dQosDscpMutationMapAttachTable.name: dQosDscpMutationMapAttachTable
dQosDscpMutationMapAttachTable.description: This table provides a mechanism to attach a DSCP mutation map to a port.

dQosDscpMutationMapAttachEntry.name: dQosDscpMutationMapAttachEntry
dQosDscpMutationMapAttachEntry.description: An entry contains associating DSCP mutation map information.

dQosDscpMutationMapAttachName.name: dQosDscpMutationMapAttachName
dQosDscpMutationMapAttachName.description: This object indicates the name of the attached mutation map. A zero length of string indicates no mutation map is attached.

dQosDscpMapCtrlTable.name: dQosDscpMapCtrlTable
dQosDscpMapCtrlTable.description: This table contains information about the mapping of DSCP to priority and DSCP to color for mapping a packet's initial color.

dQosDscpMapCtrlEntry.name: dQosDscpMapCtrlEntry
dQosDscpMapCtrlEntry.description: An entry contains DSCP mapping information.

dQosDscpMapCtrlDscp.name: dQosDscpMapCtrlDscp
dQosDscpMapCtrlDscp.description: This object indicates the DSCP of the entry.

dQosDscpMapCtrlCos.name: dQosDscpMapCtrlCos
dQosDscpMapCtrlCos.description: This object indicates the mapped CoS value. Default mapping is: DSCP CoS 0-7 0 8-15 1 16-23 2 24-31 3 32-39 4 40-47 5 48-55 6 56-63 7

dQosDscpMapCtrlColor.name: dQosDscpMapCtrlColor
dQosDscpMapCtrlColor.description: This object indicates the mapped color to determine a packet's initial color.

dQosCosToColorMapTable.name: dQosCosToColorMapTable
dQosCosToColorMapTable.description: A table contains information about the mapping of CoS to color.

dQosCosToColorMapEntry.name: dQosCosToColorMapEntry
dQosCosToColorMapEntry.description: An entry contains a mapping between CoS to color.

dQosCosMapCos.name: dQosCosMapCos
dQosCosMapCos.description: This object indicates the CoS of the entry.

dQosCosMapColor.name: dQosCosMapColor
dQosCosMapColor.description: This object indicates the mapped color to determine a packet's initial color.

dQosCosToQueueMapTable.name: dQosCosToQueueMapTable
dQosCosToQueueMapTable.description: A table contains information about the mapping of CoS to queue.

dQosCosToQueueMapEntry.name: dQosCosToQueueMapEntry
dQosCosToQueueMapEntry.description: An entry contains a mapping between CoS to queue.

dQosCosToQueueCos.name: dQosCosToQueueCos
dQosCosToQueueCos.description: This object indicates the CoS of the entry.

dQosCosToQueueQID.name: dQosCosToQueueQID
dQosCosToQueueQID.description: This object indicates the queue ID that the corresponding CoS will be queued.

dQosAggPolicerTable.name: dQosAggPolicerTable
dQosAggPolicerTable.description: This table consists of a list of aggregate policers.

dQosAggPolicerEntry.name: dQosAggPolicerEntry
dQosAggPolicerEntry.description: This entry consists of information and configurations for an aggregate policer.

dQosAggPolicerName.name: dQosAggPolicerName
dQosAggPolicerName.description: This object indicates the name of the aggregate policer.

dQosAggPolicerType.name: dQosAggPolicerType
dQosAggPolicerType.description: This object indicates how meters a packet stream and marks its packets. This object determines which other objects in the same row are meaningful. trTcm - two rate three color marker; singleRate - There are two kinds of single rate policers: a. single rate three color (srTcm) - if the violate action is specified b. single rate two color - if the violate action is not specified.

dQosAggPolicerCir.name: dQosAggPolicerCir
dQosAggPolicerCir.description: This object is interpreted within the context of dQosAggPolicerType. The measurement unit is in kilobits per second. dQosAggPolicerType dQosAggPolicerCir ================== =============================================== 'trTcm' The committed information rate for first token bucket. 'singleRate' The rate-limit for two-color policier. Or: The committed information rate for srTcm.

dQosAggPolicerCbs.name: dQosAggPolicerCbs
dQosAggPolicerCbs.description: This object is interpreted within the context of dQosAggPolicerType. dQosAggPolicerType dQosAggPolicerCbs ================== =============================================== 'trTcm' The burst size for the first token bucket. 'singleRate' The burst size for two-color policier. Or: The committed burst size for srTcm. The measurement unit is in kilobytes. The special value of 0 is used to indicate this object is not specified and the default value will be used. What's the default value is project-dependent.

dQosAggPolicerSrtcmEbs.name: dQosAggPolicerSrtcmEbs
dQosAggPolicerSrtcmEbs.description: This object indicates the excess burst size for srTcm and is meaningless when dQosAggPolicerType is 'trTcm'. The measurement unit is in kilobytes. The special value of 0 is used to indicate this object is not specified and the default value will be used. What's the default value is project-dependent.

dQosAggPolicerTrtcmPir.name: dQosAggPolicerTrtcmPir
dQosAggPolicerTrtcmPir.description: This object indicates the peak information rate for the second token bucket for the two-rate metering. This object is only meaningful when dQosAggPolicerType is 'trTcm'. The measurement unit is in kilobits per second. The special value of 0 is used to indicate this object is not specified and the default value will be used. What's the default value is project-dependent.

dQosAggPolicerTrtcmPbs.name: dQosAggPolicerTrtcmPbs
dQosAggPolicerTrtcmPbs.description: This object indicates the burst size for the second token bucket. This object is meaningful only when dQosAggPolicerType is 'trTcm'. The measurement unit is in kilobytes. The special value of 0 is used to indicate this object is not specified and the default value will be used. What's the default value is project-dependent.

dQosAggPolicerConformAction.name: dQosAggPolicerConformAction
dQosAggPolicerConformAction.description: This object indicates the action when the packet is in 'green color'.

dQosAggPolicerConformReplaceDscp.name: dQosAggPolicerConformReplaceDscp
dQosAggPolicerConformReplaceDscp.description: This object indicates the new DSCP value of the packet when packet is in 'green color'. This object is meaningful only when dQosAggPolicerConformAction is 'replaceDscp' or 'replaceAll'.

dQosAggPolicerExceedAction.name: dQosAggPolicerExceedAction
dQosAggPolicerExceedAction.description: This object is interpreted within the context of dQosAggPolicerType. dQosAggPolicerType dQosAggPolExceedAction ================== =============================================== 'trTcm' The action to take for those packets that conform to PIR but not to CIR. 'singleRate' The action to take on the packets exceed the rate limit (or committed burst size).

dQosAggPolicerExceedReplaceDscp.name: dQosAggPolicerExceedReplaceDscp
dQosAggPolicerExceedReplaceDscp.description: This object indicates the new DSCP value when dQosAggPolExceedAction is 'replaceDscp'or 'replaceAll'.

dQosAggPolicerViolateAction.name: dQosAggPolicerViolateAction
dQosAggPolicerViolateAction.description: This object indicates the action state when the packet is in 'red color'.

dQosAggPolicerViolateReplaceDscp.name: dQosAggPolicerViolateReplaceDscp
dQosAggPolicerViolateReplaceDscp.description: This object indicates the DSCP value of the packet when packet is in 'red color'. This object is meaningful only when dQosAggPolicerViolateAction is 'replaceDscp' or 'replaceAll'.

dQosAggPolicerColorAware.name: dQosAggPolicerColorAware
dQosAggPolicerColorAware.description: This object indicates whether the policer is color aware or not.

dQosAggPolicerRowStatus.name: dQosAggPolicerRowStatus
dQosAggPolicerRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

dQosAggPolicerConformReplaceCos.name: dQosAggPolicerConformReplaceCos
dQosAggPolicerConformReplaceCos.description: This object indicates the new COS value of the packet when packet is in 'green color'. This object is meaningful only when dQosAggPolicerConformAction is 'replaceCos' or 'replaceAll'.

dQosAggPolicerExceedReplaceCos.name: dQosAggPolicerExceedReplaceCos
dQosAggPolicerExceedReplaceCos.description: This object indicates the new COS value when dQosAggPolExceedAction is 'replaceCos'or 'replaceAll'.

dQosAggPolicerViolateReplaceCos.name: dQosAggPolicerViolateReplaceCos
dQosAggPolicerViolateReplaceCos.description: This object indicates the COS value of the packet when packet is in 'red color'. This object is meaningful only when dQosAggPolicerViolateAction is 'replaceCos' or 'replaceAll'.

dQosPoliceTable.name: dQosPoliceTable
dQosPoliceTable.description: This table is used to configure the metering function. Users may set the preferred bandwidth for this rule; once the bandwidth has been exceeded, overflow packets will be either dropped or set for a drop precedence, depending on user configuration.

dQosPoliceEntry.name: dQosPoliceEntry
dQosPoliceEntry.description: This entry consists of configurations for the metering policing for a traffic class in a policy map.

dQosPoliceType.name: dQosPoliceType
dQosPoliceType.description: This object indicates the type of policer used for a traffic class in a policy map. This object determines which other objects in the same row are meaningful. trTcm - two rate three color marker; singleRate - There are two kinds of single rate policers: a. single rate three color (srTcm) - if the violate action is specified b. single rate two color - if the violate action is not specified. aggregate - uses a named aggregate policer as the policy. In this case, except index elements, dQosAggPolicer, and dQosPoliceRowStatus, other elements in the same row are not applicable.

dQosPoliceNamedAggPolicer.name: dQosPoliceNamedAggPolicer
dQosPoliceNamedAggPolicer.description: This object indicates the name of the aggregate policer to be applied. This object is meaningful only when dQosPoliceType is 'aggregate'.

dQosPoliceCir.name: dQosPoliceCir
dQosPoliceCir.description: This object is interpreted within the context of dQosPoliceType. The measurement unit is in kilobits per second. dQosPoliceType dQosPoliceCir ================== =============================================== 'trTcm' The committed information rate for first token bucket. 'singleRate' The rate-limit for two-color policier. Or: The committed information rate for srTcm. 'aggregate' Not applicable

dQosPoliceCbs.name: dQosPoliceCbs
dQosPoliceCbs.description: This object is interpreted within the context of dQosPoliceType. dQosPoliceType dQosPoliceCbs ================== =============================================== 'trTcm' The burst size for the first token bucket. 'singleRate' The burst size for two-color policier. Or: The committed burst size for srTcm. 'aggregate' Not applicable The measurement unit is in kilobytes. The special value of 0 is used to indicate this object is not specified and the default value will be used. What's the default value is project-dependent.

dQosPoliceSrtcmEbs.name: dQosPoliceSrtcmEbs
dQosPoliceSrtcmEbs.description: This object indicates the excess burst size for srTcm and is meaningless when dQosPoliceType is 'trTcm'. The measurement unit is in kilobytes. The special value of 0 is used to indicate this object is not specified and the default value will be used. What's the default value is project-dependent.

dQosPoliceTrtcmPir.name: dQosPoliceTrtcmPir
dQosPoliceTrtcmPir.description: This object indicates the peak information rate for the second token bucket for the two-rate metering. This object is only meaningful when dQosPoliceType is 'trTcm'. The measurement unit is in kilobits per second. The special value of 0 is used to indicate this object is not specified and the default value will be used. What's the default value is project-dependent.

dQosPoliceTrtcmPbs.name: dQosPoliceTrtcmPbs
dQosPoliceTrtcmPbs.description: This object indicates the burst size for the second token bucket. This object is meaningful only when dQosPoliceType is 'trTcm'. The measurement unit is in kilobytes. The special value of 0 is used to indicate this object is not specified and the default value will be used. What's the default value is project-dependent.

dQosPoliceConformAction.name: dQosPoliceConformAction
dQosPoliceConformAction.description: This object indicates the action when the packet is in 'green color'.

dQosPoliceConformReplaceDscp.name: dQosPoliceConformReplaceDscp
dQosPoliceConformReplaceDscp.description: This object indicates the new DSCP value for dQosPoliceConformAction is 'replaceDscp' or 'replaceAll'.

dQosPoliceExceedAction.name: dQosPoliceExceedAction
dQosPoliceExceedAction.description: This object is interpreted within the context of dQosPoliceType. dQosPoliceType dQosPoliceExceedAction ================== =============================================== 'trTcm' The action to take for those packets that conform to PIR but not to CIR. 'singleRate' The action to take on the packets exceed the rate limit (or committed burst size). 'aggregate' Not applicable

dQosPoliceExceedReplaceDscp.name: dQosPoliceExceedReplaceDscp
dQosPoliceExceedReplaceDscp.description: This object indicates the new DSCP value when dQosPoliceExceedAction is 'replaceDscp' or 'replaceAll'.

dQosPoliceViolateAction.name: dQosPoliceViolateAction
dQosPoliceViolateAction.description: This object indicates the action state when the packet is in 'red color'.

dQosPoliceViolateReplaceDscp.name: dQosPoliceViolateReplaceDscp
dQosPoliceViolateReplaceDscp.description: This object indicates the new DSCP value when dQosPoliceViolateAction is 'replaceDscp' or 'replaceAll'.

dQosPoliceColorAware.name: dQosPoliceColorAware
dQosPoliceColorAware.description: This object indicates whether the policer is color aware or not. This object is applied for dQosPoliceType is 'trTcm' or 'singleRate'.

dQosPoliceRowStatus.name: dQosPoliceRowStatus
dQosPoliceRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

dQosPoliceConformReplaceCos.name: dQosPoliceConformReplaceCos
dQosPoliceConformReplaceCos.description: This object indicates the new COS value for dQosPoliceConformAction is 'replaceCos' or 'replaceAll'.

dQosPoliceExceedReplaceCos.name: dQosPoliceExceedReplaceCos
dQosPoliceExceedReplaceCos.description: This object indicates the new COS value when dQosPoliceExceedAction is 'replaceCos' or 'replaceAll'.

dQosPoliceViolateReplaceCos.name: dQosPoliceViolateReplaceCos
dQosPoliceViolateReplaceCos.description: This object indicates the new COS value when dQosPoliceViolateAction is 'replaceCos' or 'replaceAll'.
